Here's the refactor, with each change tied to the finding that motivates it.

## Refactored `src/Card.tsx`

```tsx
import styles from "./Card.module.css";

export function Card({
  children,
  onActivate,
  label,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  onActivate: () => void;
  label: string;
}) {
  return (
    <button type="button" className={styles.card} onClick={onActivate} aria-label={label}>
      <div className={styles.body}>{children}</div>
      <aside className={styles.sidebar}>sidebar</aside>
    </button>
  );
}
```

```css
/* Card.module.css */
.card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 240px);
  gap: var(--space-4);
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--size-card-max, 64rem);
  padding: var(--space-6);
  background: var(--color-surface-accent);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-muted);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  outline-color: var(--color-focus-ring);
  text-align: left;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.body { font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.4vw, 1.125rem); }
.sidebar { font-size: var(--font-size-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); }

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

## How each change maps to a finding

**`accessible_interaction_risk` (crime_00001)** ‚Äî the `<div onClick>` on line 10 becomes a real `<button type="button">` with an `aria-label`. That makes it focusable, Enter/Space activatable, and screen-reader-discoverable for free; no `role="button"` / `tabIndex={0}` patch needed. The handler is lifted to an `onActivate` prop so the call site owns the semantic action.

**`design_token_escape` (crime_00002)** ‚Äî every hex/rgb literal on lines 16‚Äì20 and 24/27 (`#ff00aa`, `#0a0a0a`, `#cccccc`, `rgb(0,0,0)`, `#1a73e8`, `#333333`, `#666666`) is replaced with theme variables (`--color-surface-accent`, `--color-text-primary`, `--color-border-muted`, `--shadow-sm`, `--color-focus-ring`, `--color-text-muted`). Spacing (`24`) and radii move to `--space-*` / `--radius-md`. An agent extending the file can no longer copy a raw color forward ‚Äî there are no raw colors left to copy.

**`responsive_fragility` (crime_00003)** ‚Äî the three fixed widths (`width: 800`, inner `width: 720`, inner `width: 240`) are gone. The card becomes `width: 100%` with a `max-width` ceiling; the two-column body/sidebar is a `grid-template-columns` rule that collapses to a single column at `‚â§640px` via the new `@media` query. The 18px body font becomes a `clamp()` so it scales fluidly instead of hard-snapping at small viewports.

## Caveats

- The `onActivate` / `label` props are a behavior change at the call site ‚Äî every existing `<Card>` caller needs to pass them. If the click was vestigial (the fixture only logs), an alternative is to drop the handler entirely and keep `<Card>` as a plain `<section aria-label={label}>`. I'd want to know which before landing this.
- The CSS variables above assume tokens exist in the design system. If the project doesn't have a token layer yet, that's a prerequisite phase, not part of this file's refactor.
